{
    "surah":  84,
    "name_ar":  "سُورَةُ الانشِقَاقِ",
    "name_en":  "The Splitting Open",
    "revelation":  "Meccan",
    "verses":  [
                   {
                       "ayah":  1,
                       "arabic":  "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ إِذَا ٱلسَّمَآءُ ٱنشَقَّتْ",
                       "english":  "When the sky has split [open]"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  2,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَذِنَتْ لِرَبِّهَا وَحُقَّتْ",
                       "english":  "And has responded to its Lord and was obligated [to do so]"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  3,
                       "arabic":  "وَإِذَا ٱلْأَرْضُ مُدَّتْ",
                       "english":  "And when the earth has been extended"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  4,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَلْقَتْ مَا فِيهَا وَتَخَلَّتْ",
                       "english":  "And has cast out that within it and relinquished [it]"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  5,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَذِنَتْ لِرَبِّهَا وَحُقَّتْ",
                       "english":  "And has responded to its Lord and was obligated [to do so] -"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  6,
                       "arabic":  "يَٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلْإِنسَٰنُ إِنَّكَ كَادِحٌ إِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ كَدْحًۭا فَمُلَٰقِيهِ",
                       "english":  "O mankind, indeed you are laboring toward your Lord with [great] exertion and will meet it."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  7,
                       "arabic":  "فَأَمَّا مَنْ أُوتِىَ كِتَٰبَهُۥ بِيَمِينِهِۦ",
                       "english":  "Then as for he who is given his record in his right hand,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  8,
                       "arabic":  "فَسَوْفَ يُحَاسَبُ حِسَابًۭا يَسِيرًۭا",
                       "english":  "He will be judged with an easy account"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  9,
                       "arabic":  "وَيَنقَلِبُ إِلَىٰٓ أَهْلِهِۦ مَسْرُورًۭا",
                       "english":  "And return to his people in happiness."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  10,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَمَّا مَنْ أُوتِىَ كِتَٰبَهُۥ وَرَآءَ ظَهْرِهِۦ",
                       "english":  "But as for he who is given his record behind his back,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  11,
                       "arabic":  "فَسَوْفَ يَدْعُوا۟ ثُبُورًۭا",
                       "english":  "He will cry out for destruction"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  12,
                       "arabic":  "وَيَصْلَىٰ سَعِيرًا",
                       "english":  "And [enter to] burn in a Blaze."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  13,
                       "arabic":  "إِنَّهُۥ كَانَ فِىٓ أَهْلِهِۦ مَسْرُورًا",
                       "english":  "Indeed, he had [once] been among his people in happiness;"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  14,
                       "arabic":  "إِنَّهُۥ ظَنَّ أَن لَّن يَحُورَ",
                       "english":  "Indeed, he had thought he would never return [to Allah]."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  15,
                       "arabic":  "بَلَىٰٓ إِنَّ رَبَّهُۥ كَانَ بِهِۦ بَصِيرًۭا",
                       "english":  "But yes! Indeed, his Lord was ever of him, Seeing."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  16,
                       "arabic":  "فَلَآ أُقْسِمُ بِٱلشَّفَقِ",
                       "english":  "So I swear by the twilight glow"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  17,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلَّيْلِ وَمَا وَسَقَ",
                       "english":  "And [by] the night and what it envelops"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  18,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلْقَمَرِ إِذَا ٱتَّسَقَ",
                       "english":  "And [by] the moon when it becomes full"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  19,
                       "arabic":  "لَتَرْكَبُنَّ طَبَقًا عَن طَبَقٍۢ",
                       "english":  "[That] you will surely experience state after state."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  20,
                       "arabic":  "فَمَا لَهُمْ لَا يُؤْمِنُونَ",
                       "english":  "So what is [the matter] with them [that] they do not believe,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  21,
                       "arabic":  "وَإِذَا قُرِئَ عَلَيْهِمُ ٱلْقُرْءَانُ لَا يَسْجُدُونَ ۩",
                       "english":  "And when the Qur\u0027an is recited to them, they do not prostrate [to Allah]?"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  22,
                       "arabic":  "بَلِ ٱلَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا۟ يُكَذِّبُونَ",
                       "english":  "But those who have disbelieved deny,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  23,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱللَّهُ أَعْلَمُ بِمَا يُوعُونَ",
                       "english":  "And Allah is most knowing of what they keep within themselves."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  24,
                       "arabic":  "فَبَشِّرْهُم بِعَذَابٍ أَلِيمٍ",
                       "english":  "So give them tidings of a painful punishment,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  25,
                       "arabic":  "إِلَّا ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوا۟ وَعَمِلُوا۟ ٱلصَّٰلِحَٰتِ لَهُمْ أَجْرٌ غَيْرُ مَمْنُونٍۭ",
                       "english":  "Except for those who believe and do righteous deeds. For them is a reward uninterrupted."
                   }
               ]
}